The paper proposes a deep learning framework for the active sensing problem, which involves making active choices about what and when to observe in a medical setting. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the framework involves using two networks to select and predict observations, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) or neural networks (cs.NE) may also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves real-world medical datasets, which suggests that the sub-category of medical imaging (cs.SI) may also be relevant.
